    "summary": "Although 100% Frisian by birth, I feel like a Dutchman topped with a Belgian sauce: I studied in Leuven and worked in Brussels for 16 years. When I drink a Jupiler and close my eyes, I am on the \u2018Grand Place\u2019 in Brussels.\n\nI am a friendly and easy-going person who likes to be active. Sailing, windsurfing and walking in Zeeland makes me one with nature. Happily married with my first real love: we adore our sons. I keep myself fit in the swim and gym.\n\nOver the last 30 years I\u2019ve had the privilege to work:\n- Two thirds with Generale Bank/Fortis and one third with ABN AMRO\n- Half of my career in Brussels and the other half in Rotterdam and Amsterdam\n- For three quarters with Risk Management and for a fourth with Business Management\n- Well distributed over Commercial (& Institutional) Banking and ECT Energy & Transportation\n- Both as a manager and a \u2018one-man factory\u2019, supporting the businesses\n\nI dare to call myself a seasoned banker and professional in credit risk & business management: connecting easily and well respected. I understand key priorities and what to do, and  pro-actively follow up in a structured and very pragmatic way.\n\nNow I enjoy a material career pause: coach training for general development (Coach College de Baak), construction work at home, volunteer work, lots of sports and family time.\n\nI am exploring the opportunities after my career pause: become a teacher/lecturer or professional coach, run a bed & breakfast, set up a meeting & wedding farm location, work in healthcare, green banking etcetera. I am open to a lot. Making up my mind now. \n\nCheers!",
